<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,689]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenzuela-Lopez, Cano, Crous, Guarro &amp; Stchigel" authorityYear="2017" box="[289,420,266,292]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[289,420,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a poorly studied genus with only two species 
<emphasis box="[944,975,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">viz</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1114,267,292]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eupyrena">
<emphasis box="[987,1114,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">J. eupyrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Species Fungorum 2021)" baseAuthorityName="Species Fungorum" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kolkmaniorum">
<emphasis box="[1165,1352,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">J. kolkmaniorum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Species Fungorum" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" refId="ref16155" refString="Species Fungorum. (2021) Available from: https: // www. speciesfungorum. org / Names / Names. asp (accessed 12 January 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Species Fungorum 2021</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[340,582,302,328]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eupyrena">
<emphasis box="[340,582,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma eupyrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark green colonies becoming black due to chlamydospore formation on Oatmeal Agar (
<collectionCode box="[305,350,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">OA</collectionCode>
), while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Species Fungorum" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[437,624,338,364]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kolkmaniorum">
<emphasis box="[437,624,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">J. kolkmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an isabelline to olivaceous colony. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasanthika, G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[1059,1333,338,364]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis box="[1059,1333,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[1347,1452,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">KUMCC</collectionCode>
20-0227) has smoke grey to olivaceous grey colonies becoming pale brown to brownish yellow at the margin on 
<collectionCode box="[1388,1448,374,400]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
. Both 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Species Fungorum" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[196,383,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kolkmaniorum">
<emphasis box="[196,383,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">J. kolkmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[435,563,411,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eupyrena">
<emphasis box="[435,563,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">J. eupyrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have conidia-bearing pycnidia on cultures in OA (
<bibRefCitation author="Valenzuela-Lopez, N. &amp; Cano-Lira, J. F. &amp; Guarro, J. &amp; Sutton, D. A. &amp; Wiederhold, N. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; Stchigel, A. M." box="[1118,1447,410,437]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref16779" refString="Valenzuela-Lopez, N., Cano-Lira, J. F., Guarro, J., Sutton, D. A., Wiederhold, N., Crous, P. W. &amp; Stchigel, A. M. (2018) Coelomycetous Dothideomycetes with emphasis on the families Cucurbitariaceae and Didymellaceae. Studies in Mycology 90: 1 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. simyco. 2017.11.003" type="journal article" year="2018">
Valenzuela-Lopez 
<emphasis box="[1328,1376,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, L. &amp; Hernandez-Restrepo, M. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Cai, L. &amp; Crous, P. W." box="[136,320,446,473]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" pagination="49 - 99" refId="ref11808" refString="Hou, L., Hernandez-Restrepo, M., Groenewald, J. Z., Cai, L. &amp; Crous, P. W. (2020) Citizen science project reveals high diversity in Didymellaceae (Pleosporales, Dothideomycetes). MycoKeys 65: 49 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / mycokeys. 65.47704" type="journal article" year="2020">
Hou 
<emphasis box="[193,243,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). However, we did not see any pycnidial formation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasanthika, G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[942,1219,446,472]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis box="[942,1219,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[1236,1341,446,472]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">KUMCC</collectionCode>
20-0227) colonies in 
<collectionCode box="[264,324,482,508]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yasanthika, G. C. Ren &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[491,766,482,508]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis box="[491,766,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[780,885,482,508]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">KUMCC</collectionCode>
20-0227) has abundant chlamydospores formation on 
<collectionCode box="[173,227,518,544]" country="Sri Lanka" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13944" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" type="Herbarium">PDA</collectionCode>
culture, which is a common character to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenzuela-Lopez, Cano, Crous, Guarro &amp; Stchigel" authorityYear="2017" box="[705,836,518,544]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[705,836,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Valenzuela-Lopez, N. &amp; Cano-Lira, J. F. &amp; Guarro, J. &amp; Sutton, D. A. &amp; Wiederhold, N. &amp; Crous, P. W. &amp; Stchigel, A. M." box="[852,1190,518,545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref16779" refString="Valenzuela-Lopez, N., Cano-Lira, J. F., Guarro, J., Sutton, D. A., Wiederhold, N., Crous, P. W. &amp; Stchigel, A. M. (2018) Coelomycetous Dothideomycetes with emphasis on the families Cucurbitariaceae and Didymellaceae. Studies in Mycology 90: 1 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. simyco. 2017.11.003" type="journal article" year="2018">
Valenzuela-Lopez 
<emphasis box="[1065,1116,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, L. &amp; Hernandez-Restrepo, M. &amp; Groenewald, J. Z. &amp; Cai, L. &amp; Crous, P. W." box="[1203,1388,518,545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" pagination="49 - 99" refId="ref11808" refString="Hou, L., Hernandez-Restrepo, M., Groenewald, J. Z., Cai, L. &amp; Crous, P. W. (2020) Citizen science project reveals high diversity in Didymellaceae (Pleosporales, Dothideomycetes). MycoKeys 65: 49 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / mycokeys. 65.47704" type="journal article" year="2020">
Hou 
<emphasis box="[1260,1311,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). The combined phylogenetic analysis (ITS-LSU- 
<emphasis box="[626,724,554,581]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">btub -rpb</emphasis>
2) indicates that our new strain constitutes a distant lineage from 
<taxonomicName box="[136,378,590,616]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="eupyrena">
<emphasis box="[136,378,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Juxtiphoma eupyrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Species Fungorum" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[434,624,590,616]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="kolkmaniorum">
<emphasis box="[434,624,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">J. kolkmaniorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 99% 
<collectionCode box="[748,793,591,617]" country="France" name="Musee de Lectoure" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">ML</collectionCode>
, 1.00 
<collectionCode box="[862,931,591,617]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">BYPP</collectionCode>
statistical support (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1276,590,616]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1884,1906]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,283,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-64@7.[151,1436,278,1855]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. RAxML tree inferred from the combined dataset of ITS-LSU-rpb2-btub partial sequences of strains of Didymellaceae. Bootstrap support values for maximum likelihood (ML) values equal to or higher than 60% and Bayesian posterior probabilities (BYPP) equal to or greater than 0.95 are given above each branch, respectively. The new isolate is in blue bold. Ex-type strains are in black bold. The tree is rooted to Leptosphaeria conoidea (CBS 616.75) and L. doliolum (CBS 505.75). The scale bar represents the expected number of nucleotide substitutions per site 0.08." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5312448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5312448/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">FIGURE 1</figureCitation>
). We introduce this novel lineage as 
<emphasis box="[372,741,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">
<taxonomicName authority="Yasanthika &amp; Wanasinghe &amp; Ren &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Tennakoon &amp; Monkai &amp; Gui &amp; Mortimer &amp; Lumyong &amp; Hyde, 2021" authorityName="Yasanthika &amp; Wanasinghe &amp; Ren &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Tennakoon &amp; Monkai &amp; Gui &amp; Mortimer &amp; Lumyong &amp; Hyde" authorityYear="2021" box="[372,648,626,652]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Didymellaceae" genus="Juxtiphoma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="yunnanensis" status="sp. nov.">Juxtiphoma yunnanensis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[656,741,627,652]" pageId="11" pageNumber="214" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, which was isolated from industrial waste-contaminated soil in Kunming City, 
<collectingRegion box="[308,503,662,689]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[514,585,662,688]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="214">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
